'''Mariana Avitia Mart<U+00ED>nez''' (born September 18, 1993 in [[Monterrey]], [[Nuevo Le<U+00F3>n]]) is an athlete from [[Mexico]] who competes in [[archery]].  

==2008 Summer Olympics==
At the [[2008 Summer Olympics]] in [[Beijing]] Avitia finished her ranking round with a total of 641 points. This gave her the 20th seed for the final competition bracket in which she faced [[Son Hye-Yong]] in the first round, beating the archer from [[North Korea]] with 112-107. In the second round she was too strong for [[Malgorzata Cwienczek]] with 110-109 and via [[Khatuna Narimanidze]] (109-108) she achieved her place in the quarter final. There she was eliminated by [[Kwon Un-Sil]] with 105-99.<ref name="beijing">[http://results.beijing2008.cn/WRM/ENG/BIO/Athlete/8/240818.shtml Athlete biography: Mariana Avitia], beijing2008.cn, ret: Aug, 23 2008</ref>

==2012 Summer Olympics==
At the 2012 Summer Olympics in London Avitia finished third to win the first medal for Mexico in the country's archery history for both Male and Female.

